If you have "show logical structures" turned on, then the evaluation that is 
requried to show the logical structure can cause this to happen (a GC has 
collected a temporary object we were using for an evaluation).

*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 33452 ***

#33452 is RESOLVED as (FIXED) RESOLVE LATER. What does this mean?
Does this mean that it won't be fixed? I really that is it because this bug is
very annoying - even if it is not critical - since it happens all the time. One
cannot use "show logical structures" that is.

It's RESOLVED - LATER (*not* FIXED). This means that we agree it's a problem, 
but that we are not committed to fixing it in the next release. The reason in 
this specific case is that we do not have a good/known solution to the problem.
